ENTRY            M0739   20260121   20260302   20260302       M144
SUBENT        M0739001   20260121   20260302   20260302       M144
BIB                 14         43
TITLE      12C(gamma-pol,pn) photon asymmetry for
            Eg = 180 - 340 MeV.
AUTHOR     (S.Franczuk,I.J.D.Macgregor,J.Ahrens,J.R.M.Annand,
           J.F.Arneil,R.Beck,D.Dranford,P.Grabmayr,S.J.Hall,
           T.Hehl,P.D.Harty,D.G.Ireland,J.D.Kellie, K.Livingston,
           J.C.Mcgeorge,F.A.Natter,S.Oberkirsch, R.O.Owens,
           C.J.Y.Powrie,J.Ryckebusch,M.Sauer, A.Settele,D.P.Watts)
REFERENCE  (J,PL/B,450,332,1999)
           #doi:10.1016/S0370-2693(99)00184-7
INSTITUTE  (2UK GLS,2UK EDG,2GERTUE,2GERMNZ,2BLGGHT)
FACILITY   (MICRT,2GERMNZ) Mainz 855 MeV electron microtron MAMI.
INC-SOURCE (TAGD) Glasgow tagged photon spectrometer linearly
            polarized photons, maximum polarization produced was
            ~ 65% and data with polarizations greater than 25%
            were analysed.
SAMPLE     0.7 g/cm2 graphite target inclined at the angle  of
            30 deg.
METHOD     (TOF,COINC)
DETECTOR   (SCIN) For protons - plastic scintillator hodoscope
            with ~ 1 sr solid angle, covering proton polar angle
            from 50 to 130 deg and azimuthal angles of +- 22 deg.
            For neutrons correlated with protons - array of
            plastic scintillator time-of-flight detectors,
            deployed on the opposite side of photon beam between
            polar angles of 28 and 148 deg, the azimuthal angular
            coverage was always 13.5 - 22 deg.
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-S) Statistical errors due to random sampling of
            the experimental kinematics.
COMMENT    The photon asymmetry of the 12C(gamma-pol,pn) reaction
            has been measured for separate missing energy regions
            corresponding to the ejection of nucleons from
            (1p)**2 and (1p)(1s) shells.
ANG-SEC    (ANG1-MIN,G)
           (ANG1-MAX,G)
           (ANG2-MIN,P)
           (ANG2-MAX,P)
STATUS     (CURVE,,S.Franczuk+,J,PL/B,450,332,1999)
            Data from Fig. 1.
HISTORY    (20080227C) Compiled at the Russia MSU SINP CDFE by
            V.Varlamov.
           (20110119A) Corrected by V.Varlamov: REFERENCE,
           NOCOMMON in 002.
           (20260121U) Corrected by VV and SD: ANG-SEC, STATUS.
ENDBIB              43
COMMON               5          3
EN-RSL     ANG1-MIN   ANG1-MAX   ANG2-MIN   ANG2-MAX
MEV        ADEG       ADEG       ADEG       ADEG
         2.        28.       148.        50.       130.
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           50
SUBENT        M0739002   20110119   20110323   20110311       M056
BIB                  2          4
REACTION   (6-C-12(G,N+P)5-B-10,,POL/DA,,ASY/PP)
            Polarised photons.
            Nucleons from (1p)**2 shell.
MISC-COL   (MISC) Data for nucleons from (1p)(1s) shell.
ENDBIB               4
NOCOMMON             0          0
DATA                 5          5
EN         DATA       ERR-S      MISC       MISC-ERR
MEV        NO-DIM     NO-DIM     NO-DIM     NO-DIM
   180.      -0.0758      .0348    -0.1795    .0455
   220.      -0.1818      .0341    -0.127     .0303
   260.      -0.1515      .028     -0.1061    .0303
   300.      -0.197       .0621    -0.1288    .0564
   340.      -0.2386      .0492    -0.1894    .0417
ENDDATA              7
ENDSUBENT           16
ENDENTRY             2
